{"questionId":"9077074","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A rocket of proper length 120 m moves to the right with speed 0.82<em>c</em> relative to the ground.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/4de8a16c0efec80b9692479701077e59712b479b.png\"></p>\n<p>A probe is released from the back of the rocket at speed 0.40<em>c</em> relative to the rocket.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the speed of the probe relative to the ground.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{0.82c + 0.40c}}{{1 + \\frac{{0.82c \\times 0.40c}}{{{c^2}}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.82</mn>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>0.40</mn>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>0.82</mn>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mo>×</mo>\n          <mn>0.40</mn>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>c</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>0.92<em>c</em> ✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9077074","referenceCode":"18N.3.SL.TZ0.a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the speed of the probe relative to the ground.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.2 – Lorentz transformations","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}